<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb8c1da0b-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8" identifier="/us/usc/t18/s229C"><num value="229C">§ 229C.</num><heading> Individual self-defense devices</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to prohibit any individual self-defense device, including those using a pepper spray or chemical mace.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb8c1da0c-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/105/277/dI/tII/s201/a">Pub. L. 105–277, div. I, title II, § 201(a)</ref>, <date date="1998-10-21">Oct. 21, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/2681-869">112 Stat. 2681–869</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
